// Write the address of the GOT entry to the format string
sprintf(format_string, "%%.%d$hn", offset_to_got_entry);

// Write the value to the GOT entry
sprintf(format_string, "%%.%d$hn", offset_to_got_entry + 2);
```
In this example, `offset_to_got_entry` is the offset between the address of the format string and the address of the GOT entry. We use the `%hn` format specifier to write the address of the GOT entry to the format string, and then we use the `%hn` format specifier again to write the value to the GOT entry.

**Example exploit code**

